WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.786 --> 00:00:04.178
.

2
00:00:04.221 --> 00:00:06.224
- In the criminal justice
system.

3
00:00:06.268 --> 00:00:07.791
sexually based offenses

4
00:00:07.834 --> 00:00:09.575
are considered
especially heinous.

5
00:00:09.619 --> 00:00:11.664
In New York City.
the dedicated detectives

6
00:00:11.708 --> 00:00:13.492
who investigate
these vicious felonies

7
00:00:13.536 --> 00:00:15.147
are members of an elite squad

8
00:00:15.191 --> 00:00:17.062
known as
the Special Victims Unit.

9
00:00:17.106 --> 00:00:19.804
These are their stories.

10
00:00:20.631 --> 00:00:22.937
- Notice your breath
as it flows gently

11
00:00:22.981 --> 00:00:25.245
in and out of your body.

12
00:00:25.289 --> 00:00:28.553
Let your chest rise
and fall...

13
00:00:28.596 --> 00:00:32.165
[distant indistinct shouting]

14
00:00:32.209 --> 00:00:33.862
- Are you kidding me?

15
00:00:33.906 --> 00:00:35.387
- If your thoughts wander.

16
00:00:35.430 --> 00:00:38.216
simply refocus your mind on
your breathing.

17
00:00:38.259 --> 00:00:41.219
[shouting continues]

18
00:00:41.262 --> 00:00:44.135
[tranquil music]

19
00:00:44.178 --> 00:00:46.138
- Namaste my ass.

20
00:00:46.181 --> 00:00:49.054
[shouting continues]

21
00:00:49.097 --> 00:00:53.145
- What the hell are you doing?
I can hear you in here!

22
00:00:53.188 --> 00:00:54.711
- No. you're so annoying!

23
00:00:54.755 --> 00:00:56.671
- Look. we have rules.
Mackenzie. you know that!

24
00:00:56.714 --> 00:00:58.238
- Well. I don't need rules.
They're stupid!

25
00:00:58.281 --> 00:01:00.153
- Hey! You're not going
to have this!

26
00:01:00.196 --> 00:01:02.155
- If Mom were here--
- She is not here! I am!

27
00:01:02.198 --> 00:01:03.982
- I'll give you no Snapchat.
but my phone?

28
00:01:04.026 --> 00:01:05.594
- You lost the privilege. okay?

29
00:01:05.637 --> 00:01:07.378
And it's not coming back!
What are you doing?

30
00:01:07.422 --> 00:01:08.640
- Cook your own dinner!

31
00:01:08.684 --> 00:01:10.164
- Do not throw that!
[glass shatters]

32
00:01:10.207 --> 00:01:12.122
- I hate you!
You're so annoying!

33
00:01:12.166 --> 00:01:13.689
- God damn it!

34
00:01:13.732 --> 00:01:15.344
- Are you serious?
Look at what you did!

35
00:01:15.387 --> 00:01:17.955
- Stop. stop!
[screams]

36
00:01:17.998 --> 00:01:20.392
[tense music]

37
00:01:20.436 --> 00:01:23.700
- [sighs]
It's nothing really.

38
00:01:23.743 --> 00:01:25.311
- Well. that's not what
your neighbor says.

39
00:01:25.355 --> 00:01:26.747
- Yeah. well.
she's a nosy bitch.

40
00:01:26.791 --> 00:01:28.575
always butting in
where she's not wanted.

41
00:01:28.619 --> 00:01:31.230
- That's enough.
- Are you going to arrest us?

42
00:01:31.274 --> 00:01:33.145
- It--it's just
a big misunderstanding.

43
00:01:33.189 --> 00:01:36.323
- A lot of blood and broken
glass for a misunderstanding.

44
00:01:36.367 --> 00:01:38.064
- If you just let me
call Chase.

45
00:01:38.108 --> 00:01:39.326
- Did he hit you?

46
00:01:39.370 --> 00:01:41.763
- I don't know.
Can I have my phone back?

47
00:01:45.072 --> 00:01:46.421
- Garrett Howard and
his step-daughter.

48
00:01:46.465 --> 00:01:47.901
Mackenzie Tolliver. 13.

49
00:01:47.944 --> 00:01:50.121
Neighbor said she was screaming
bloody murder.

50
00:01:50.164 --> 00:01:52.079
- Where's Mom?
- I didn't think to ask.

51
00:01:52.123 --> 00:01:53.385
It's more up your alley
anyway.

52
00:01:53.428 --> 00:01:54.560
- You suspect child abuse?

53
00:01:54.603 --> 00:01:55.910
- There was evidence
of a fight.

54
00:01:55.953 --> 00:01:57.259
She wouldn't say
if she was hurt

55
00:01:57.303 --> 00:01:58.826
and Dad cut himself on
some glass.

56
00:01:58.869 --> 00:02:00.784
Figured I'd bring 'em both
here to get checked out.

57
00:02:00.828 --> 00:02:02.960
- Okay. we'll take it
from here.

58
00:02:03.004 --> 00:02:04.788
Mr. Howard. Mackenzie.

59
00:02:04.832 --> 00:02:08.141
I'm Lieutenant Benson.
Uh. this is Detective Carisi.

60
00:02:08.184 --> 00:02:09.751
- What do you want?

61
00:02:09.794 --> 00:02:12.536
- Mr. Howard. why do--why don't
you come talk to me over here?

62
00:02:14.930 --> 00:02:16.411
- So Mackenzie--

63
00:02:16.454 --> 00:02:18.587
- Lieutenant.
you saved me a call.

64
00:02:18.630 --> 00:02:20.415
If you have a minute.
- Okay.

65
00:02:20.458 --> 00:02:22.852
Give me a moment.
I'll be right back.

66
00:02:24.245 --> 00:02:25.464
What's going on?

67
00:02:25.508 --> 00:02:26.465
- I think we may have
a problem.

68
00:02:26.509 --> 00:02:27.988
- What kind of problem?

69
00:02:28.032 --> 00:02:29.381
- The girl was pretty
hysterical when she came in.

70
00:02:29.425 --> 00:02:31.078
- Okay. did she say
what was wrong?

71
00:02:31.122 --> 00:02:32.776
- Well. I tried to give her
something to calm her down.

72
00:02:32.819 --> 00:02:35.519
She refused to take it.
- Because?

73
00:02:35.562 --> 00:02:38.783
- She thought it
would hurt her baby.

74
00:02:38.826 --> 00:02:40.828
- You're kidding me.

75
00:02:40.872 --> 00:02:43.179
She's 13 years old.

76
00:02:43.222 --> 00:02:45.660
- Thirteen and pregnant.

77
00:02:45.704 --> 00:02:52.754
♪

78
00:02:57.238 --> 00:03:00.198
[dramatic music]

79
00:03:00.241 --> 00:03:07.467
♪

80
00:03:46.901 --> 00:03:49.687
- It's my fault. right?
I should've been stricter?

81
00:03:49.730 --> 00:03:52.690
- Well. you can't lock them
in their rooms. Mr. Howard.

82
00:03:52.733 --> 00:03:54.387
- Why not?

83
00:03:54.431 --> 00:03:56.564
- Do you have any idea
who the father might be?

84
00:03:56.608 --> 00:03:57.957
- She didn't tell me
she was pregnant.

85
00:03:58.000 --> 00:03:59.741
Why would she tell me
who the father is?

86
00:03:59.785 --> 00:04:01.569
- Did Mackenzie
have a boyfriend?

87
00:04:01.613 --> 00:04:03.092
- Not that I know of.

88
00:04:03.136 --> 00:04:04.485
- Did she ever mention
any boys?

89
00:04:04.529 --> 00:04:05.879
Maybe somebody she went
to school with.

90
00:04:05.922 --> 00:04:07.794
could've been somebody
she met online.

91
00:04:09.622 --> 00:04:12.277
- What do I know about
raising a girl?

92
00:04:12.320 --> 00:04:13.626
You know. it was stupid

93
00:04:13.669 --> 00:04:15.890
to think that
I could replace Angela.

94
00:04:15.933 --> 00:04:18.109
- Is that her mother?
- Yeah.

95
00:04:18.153 --> 00:04:19.633
She passed two years ago.

96
00:04:19.676 --> 00:04:22.200
We were only married
for a short period of time.

97
00:04:22.244 --> 00:04:23.811
[sighs]

98
00:04:23.854 --> 00:04:26.031
- So it's--it's just been
you two alone

99
00:04:26.075 --> 00:04:27.642
for the past few years?

100
00:04:29.731 --> 00:04:34.257
- I know you have to ask.
but come on. man.

101
00:04:34.301 --> 00:04:36.565
[somber music]

102
00:04:36.608 --> 00:04:39.350
I'm a father to her.

103
00:04:40.220 --> 00:04:43.267
- Stepfather.
Did you adopt Mackenzie?

104
00:04:43.311 --> 00:04:44.877
- I couldn't.

105
00:04:44.921 --> 00:04:48.447
She has a junkie father
running around somewhere.

106
00:04:48.491 --> 00:04:51.537
He and Angela divorced
when we met.

107
00:04:51.581 --> 00:04:53.844
Look. the thing is...

108
00:04:54.627 --> 00:04:58.676
I love Mackenzie
like she's my own

109
00:04:58.719 --> 00:05:00.808
and I thought I was doing
the right thing.

110
00:05:00.852 --> 00:05:02.984
- [sighs]

111
00:05:04.812 --> 00:05:07.512
- The doctor at the hospital
let me hear the heartbeat.

112
00:05:07.555 --> 00:05:09.992
It was the most unreal
feeling ever.

113
00:05:10.036 --> 00:05:12.691
- And you didn't tell
your dad?

114
00:05:12.734 --> 00:05:14.867
- Stepdad.
and I was going to.

115
00:05:14.910 --> 00:05:18.741
It's just Garrett is a little
hard to talk to sometimes.

116
00:05:18.785 --> 00:05:20.264
The baby's only
eight weeks old.

117
00:05:20.308 --> 00:05:21.918
- Did you tell
the baby's father?

118
00:05:21.962 --> 00:05:23.355
- He wouldn't care.

119
00:05:23.398 --> 00:05:25.401
- Well. how do you know that?

120
00:05:25.445 --> 00:05:27.055
- I don't want to talk
about it.

121
00:05:27.098 --> 00:05:28.404
Can I go to school now?

122
00:05:28.448 --> 00:05:29.579
I have a math quiz
and it's super important.

123
00:05:29.623 --> 00:05:31.015
- Not quite yet. Mackenzie.

124
00:05:31.059 --> 00:05:34.105
So I know that this is
difficult to talk about.

125
00:05:34.149 --> 00:05:38.807
but we need to know
the details of what happened.

126
00:05:40.199 --> 00:05:45.030
So the first question
I want to ask you is...

127
00:05:45.075 --> 00:05:48.383
were you upset about
how this happened?

128
00:05:48.426 --> 00:05:50.341
- Why do you even care?

129
00:05:50.385 --> 00:05:52.212
I'm old enough to make
my own decisions.

130
00:05:52.256 --> 00:05:53.692
- No one is saying you're not.

131
00:05:53.736 --> 00:05:56.087
We're concerned though and
your stepfather's concerned.

132
00:05:58.742 --> 00:06:01.701
- Listen. we just want
what's best for you.

133
00:06:01.745 --> 00:06:04.095
- Okay.

134
00:06:05.358 --> 00:06:06.968
He was just some guy.

135
00:06:07.012 --> 00:06:08.970
- What was his name?

136
00:06:09.014 --> 00:06:10.450
- I don't know.

137
00:06:10.494 --> 00:06:12.017
I was buying yogurt
in Whole Foods.

138
00:06:12.060 --> 00:06:13.018
We started talking.

139
00:06:13.061 --> 00:06:15.717
It was only one time
in his car.

140
00:06:15.761 --> 00:06:17.806
- So he's old enough to drive.

141
00:06:17.850 --> 00:06:19.460
- You don't understand.

142
00:06:19.504 --> 00:06:21.636
I wanted to; he didn't
force me or anything like that.

143
00:06:21.680 --> 00:06:24.073
- Listen. Mackenzie.
if he was a grown man.

144
00:06:24.117 --> 00:06:26.686
it's not okay.

145
00:06:26.729 --> 00:06:28.992
- So what color was the car?

146
00:06:29.602 --> 00:06:32.082
- It was blue.
A BMW. I think.

147
00:06:32.126 --> 00:06:34.737
- Great. that's very helpful.
Mackenzie.

148
00:06:34.781 --> 00:06:37.132
And what else can
you remember about him?

149
00:06:37.175 --> 00:06:38.916
- Why?

150
00:06:40.831 --> 00:06:44.313
- Because under the law.
Mackenzie.

151
00:06:44.356 --> 00:06:49.319
what he did to you
may be rape.

152
00:06:49.362 --> 00:06:56.588
♪

153
00:07:01.811 --> 00:07:04.161
- Is she okay?
- She's fine. considering.

154
00:07:04.204 --> 00:07:05.816
- Did she say who
the father was?

155
00:07:05.859 --> 00:07:08.427
- She said it's a man that
she met at Whole Foods.

156
00:07:08.471 --> 00:07:09.646
She doesn't know his name.

157
00:07:09.689 --> 00:07:11.343
- That's ridiculous.

158
00:07:11.386 --> 00:07:12.518
- Yeah. I know.
She's--

159
00:07:12.562 --> 00:07:13.780
she's covering for somebody.

160
00:07:13.824 --> 00:07:15.479
- Why would she do that?

161
00:07:15.522 --> 00:07:17.698
- Because she's 13 years old
and this is a lot to handle.

162
00:07:17.742 --> 00:07:21.485
- She'll come around in time.

163
00:07:21.528 --> 00:07:23.617
- Well. and if she doesn't?

164
00:07:24.792 --> 00:07:27.404
- Do you know anybody
that drives a blue BMW?

165
00:07:27.448 --> 00:07:28.841
- No.
Why?

166
00:07:28.884 --> 00:07:32.279
- Mr. Howard. would you mind
taking a look at this?

167
00:07:33.672 --> 00:07:36.414
Anybody here ring a bell?

168
00:07:36.458 --> 00:07:37.764
- Where did you get this?

169
00:07:37.807 --> 00:07:39.113
- Our computer geeks found it

170
00:07:39.156 --> 00:07:40.984
on Mackenzie's fake
Instagram account.

171
00:07:41.028 --> 00:07:43.334
- It's just an account where
she can hide stuff from you.

172
00:07:43.378 --> 00:07:48.776
- "Send nudes they said.
It'd be fun they said. lolz."

173
00:07:48.819 --> 00:07:50.517
That doesn't even sound
like Mackenzie.

174
00:07:50.560 --> 00:07:53.345
- Do you recognize them?

175
00:07:53.389 --> 00:07:55.566
- Well. they must be
from her school.

176
00:08:01.224 --> 00:08:02.660
- This is middle school.

177
00:08:02.704 --> 00:08:05.316
Our biggest problems are
cyberbullying and texting.

178
00:08:05.359 --> 00:08:06.665
not teen pregnancy.

179
00:08:06.709 --> 00:08:08.449
- Well. unfortunately
that's where we are.

180
00:08:08.493 --> 00:08:10.843
Now what can you tell us
about Mackenzie?

181
00:08:10.887 --> 00:08:13.367
- She's bright. popular.
gets good grades.

182
00:08:13.411 --> 00:08:15.153
She never gets in trouble.

183
00:08:15.196 --> 00:08:17.068
- Have you noticed
a behavioral change

184
00:08:17.111 --> 00:08:18.504
in her recently?

185
00:08:18.548 --> 00:08:19.940
- Honestly. no.

186
00:08:19.984 --> 00:08:22.029
She's always been a standout
student. super involved.

187
00:08:22.073 --> 00:08:24.423
Volleyball.
school play. art club.

188
00:08:24.466 --> 00:08:25.773
- Look. uh. is there--
is there someone

189
00:08:25.817 --> 00:08:27.079
that she could've
confided in?

190
00:08:27.122 --> 00:08:28.689
Maybe. uh. a--a close friend
or something?

191
00:08:28.733 --> 00:08:30.386
- I can ask around
but I can assure you.

192
00:08:30.430 --> 00:08:32.693
whatever happened to her
didn't happen here.

193
00:08:32.737 --> 00:08:34.216
- Okay. hey. Father.

194
00:08:34.260 --> 00:08:36.045
I need you to look at one more
thing for me. all right?

195
00:08:36.089 --> 00:08:38.178
These two boys.
they go to school here?

196
00:08:38.221 --> 00:08:39.571
- Yes. of course.

197
00:08:39.614 --> 00:08:41.834
Uh. Logan Larson
and Chase Madera.

198
00:08:41.877 --> 00:08:43.879
- Okay. we're going to need
to talk to them.

199
00:08:45.099 --> 00:08:46.491
- We were at Chase's
hanging out.

200
00:08:46.535 --> 00:08:47.623
His dad was home.

201
00:08:47.667 --> 00:08:49.712
Nothing. like.
sexual happened.

202
00:08:49.756 --> 00:08:51.801
- All right. well.
then tell me. Logan.

203
00:08:51.845 --> 00:08:57.068
why did she write that
you asked to send nudes?

204
00:08:57.112 --> 00:09:00.289
- I-I was screwing around.
I don't know.

205
00:09:00.332 --> 00:09:02.247
She never did send them.

206
00:09:02.291 --> 00:09:03.945
- Did you ever date Mackenzie?

207
00:09:03.988 --> 00:09:06.035
- No. I mean. we're friends.
you know?

208
00:09:06.078 --> 00:09:08.037
- But you thought about it.
- Sure.

209
00:09:08.080 --> 00:09:09.865
I mean...

210
00:09:09.908 --> 00:09:11.606
- Okay. listen.
I know what you mean.

211
00:09:11.649 --> 00:09:13.433
- No. it's not like that.

212
00:09:13.477 --> 00:09:16.394
Mack is just one of those girls
who is always touching you.

213
00:09:16.437 --> 00:09:18.048
- Touching how?

214
00:09:18.091 --> 00:09:20.746
- Like she puts her hand
on yours. stuff like that.

215
00:09:20.790 --> 00:09:23.401
Makes you think...

216
00:09:23.444 --> 00:09:25.273
- Makes you think what. Logan?

217
00:09:25.317 --> 00:09:28.015
- That she wants to be
closer than you really are.

218
00:09:28.059 --> 00:09:31.236
but I never did anything.

219
00:09:31.279 --> 00:09:33.412
- I used to think it was
because she was shy.

220
00:09:33.455 --> 00:09:34.761
- But now?

221
00:09:34.805 --> 00:09:38.070
- I realized she wants you
to lean in real close.

222
00:09:38.113 --> 00:09:39.506
- How close?

223
00:09:39.549 --> 00:09:40.812
- Close enough
to smell her perfume.

224
00:09:40.855 --> 00:09:42.683
It was like blueberries
or something.

225
00:09:42.727 --> 00:09:44.642
- Huh. Did you like that?

226
00:09:44.685 --> 00:09:46.645
- Sure.

227
00:09:46.688 --> 00:09:48.255
I mean. the girls around here

228
00:09:48.298 --> 00:09:49.996
aren't allowed
to wear that stuff.

229
00:09:50.039 --> 00:09:52.172
Most of them follow the rules.

230
00:09:52.215 --> 00:09:53.695
- But not Mackenzie?

231
00:09:53.739 --> 00:09:55.437
- I guess.

232
00:09:55.480 --> 00:09:58.701
- Did you ever get past the.
uh. the smelling stage?

233
00:09:58.745 --> 00:10:01.704
- I tried to kiss her a couple
of times but we never did.

234
00:10:01.748 --> 00:10:03.314
She's a tease.

235
00:10:03.358 --> 00:10:04.968
- Did that make you mad?

236
00:10:05.012 --> 00:10:06.971
- More like confused.

237
00:10:07.015 --> 00:10:09.321
Maybe the whole thing
was an act.

238
00:10:09.365 --> 00:10:13.064
- Or maybe she was
a scared 13-year-old girl.

239
00:10:13.108 --> 00:10:15.198
- Yeah. tell that to Dreyfus.

240
00:10:15.241 --> 00:10:16.721
- Who's that?

241
00:10:16.765 --> 00:10:18.462
- He teaches drama.

242
00:10:18.505 --> 00:10:20.986
but the real drama is
what goes on backstage.

243
00:10:21.030 --> 00:10:23.206
That's what I've heard anyways.

244
00:10:24.294 --> 00:10:26.776
- She's a natural.
Hey. do you mind?

245
00:10:26.819 --> 00:10:28.647
We're having a dress rehearsal
tomorrow.

246
00:10:28.691 --> 00:10:30.040
- Nah. it's all good.

247
00:10:30.083 --> 00:10:31.781
You ever worked one-on-one
with Mackenzie?

248
00:10:31.824 --> 00:10:33.826
- Alone?
Yeah. sure.

249
00:10:33.870 --> 00:10:35.089
I read lines with her.

250
00:10:35.133 --> 00:10:36.700
I do with all the students.

251
00:10:36.743 --> 00:10:39.180
- Maybe a little more often
with Mackenzie?

252
00:10:39.224 --> 00:10:41.748
- Yeah. what with her being
such a natural and all.

253
00:10:41.792 --> 00:10:44.185
- [chuckles]
You're kidding me. right?

254
00:10:44.229 --> 00:10:45.927
I would think a couple
of detectives

255
00:10:45.971 --> 00:10:47.842
would see right through
student gossip.

256
00:10:47.886 --> 00:10:50.192
Hormones set
teenage fantasies flying.

257
00:10:50.236 --> 00:10:52.804
- This may be a little more
than fantasy. Mr. Dreyfus.

258
00:10:52.847 --> 00:10:55.023
- Mackenzie Tolliver
is pregnant.

259
00:10:56.547 --> 00:10:57.810
- She's only 13.

260
00:10:57.853 --> 00:10:59.986
[dramatic music]

261
00:11:00.029 --> 00:11:02.336
Oh. my God.
You think that I'm the father.

262
00:11:02.379 --> 00:11:03.859
- Yeah.

263
00:11:03.903 --> 00:11:06.210
- Is there a reason
that we shouldn't?

264
00:11:06.254 --> 00:11:08.082
- Look. I never touched
that girl

265
00:11:08.125 --> 00:11:09.953
and anyone who says
I did is a liar.

266
00:11:09.997 --> 00:11:12.260
- What kind of car do
you drive. Mr. Dreyfus?

267
00:11:12.303 --> 00:11:14.349
- A BMW.
Why?

268
00:11:14.392 --> 00:11:16.613
♪

269
00:11:16.656 --> 00:11:18.397
- Let me guess. blue?

270
00:11:18.441 --> 00:11:21.792
♪

271
00:11:21.836 --> 00:11:24.099
- Let's go.
- Wait. am I under arrest?

272
00:11:24.142 --> 00:11:26.319
- You can be if you don't want
to come willingly.

273
00:11:26.363 --> 00:11:33.413
♪

274
00:11:37.505 --> 00:11:37.679
.

275
00:11:37.723 --> 00:11:40.117
- I've been at Saint Matthew's
for eight years.

276
00:11:40.160 --> 00:11:41.335
Why would I do something
like this now?

277
00:11:41.379 --> 00:11:42.902
- One of the great mysteries
of life.

278
00:11:42.946 --> 00:11:46.080
- You know. some guys. they--
they just like young girls.

279
00:11:46.124 --> 00:11:48.343
- The younger the better.

280
00:11:48.387 --> 00:11:50.737
- Have you asked around
the school?

281
00:11:50.781 --> 00:11:52.086
I've got a great record.

282
00:11:52.130 --> 00:11:53.696
I've never been accused
of anything like this.

283
00:11:53.740 --> 00:11:55.395
- Well. everybody's got
to start somewhere.

284
00:11:55.438 --> 00:11:57.440
- Okay. okay. you say
that she's pregnant?

285
00:11:57.484 --> 00:11:59.921
I'll give blood. DNA.
whatever you want.

286
00:12:01.705 --> 00:12:04.491
- That's exactly
what we want to hear.

287
00:12:07.016 --> 00:12:08.670
- Absolutely not.

288
00:12:08.713 --> 00:12:10.715
- I thought you wanted to know
who the father was.

289
00:12:10.759 --> 00:12:13.980
- I did. but judging by
the looks on your faces now.

290
00:12:14.023 --> 00:12:15.286
uh. I'm not so sure.

291
00:12:15.330 --> 00:12:17.332
- Even if Mackenzie was raped?

292
00:12:17.375 --> 00:12:18.986
- Look. she doesn't see it
that way

293
00:12:19.029 --> 00:12:20.378
and at this point.

294
00:12:20.422 --> 00:12:22.206
she's decided
she's keeping the baby.

295
00:12:22.250 --> 00:12:23.555
- So what?

296
00:12:23.599 --> 00:12:24.861
So--wait. wait.
you're--you're fine

297
00:12:24.905 --> 00:12:26.733
with what happened
to your daughter?

298
00:12:26.777 --> 00:12:28.039
- I have to be.

299
00:12:28.083 --> 00:12:30.912
I loved Mack's mom.
I love Mack.

300
00:12:30.955 --> 00:12:33.262
[solemn music]

301
00:12:33.305 --> 00:12:34.916
I'm in this for the long haul.

302
00:12:34.959 --> 00:12:37.223
And the last thing we need is
some stranger butting in

303
00:12:37.267 --> 00:12:40.618
and demanding rights that
he doesn't deserve.

304
00:12:40.661 --> 00:12:42.968
Look. this is
what Mackenzie wants!

305
00:12:43.012 --> 00:12:44.927
- Mackenzie's a child.

306
00:12:47.408 --> 00:12:49.367
She doesn't know
what she wants.

307
00:12:49.410 --> 00:12:51.717
- Yes. she does.

308
00:12:51.760 --> 00:12:54.546
And if that changes.
we'll reconsider.

309
00:13:00.074 --> 00:13:02.903
- So the way this usually works
is first. there's a crime.

310
00:13:02.947 --> 00:13:04.209
and then we go to court

311
00:13:04.252 --> 00:13:05.559
and we nail the person
that did it.

312
00:13:05.602 --> 00:13:07.387
- We can't tell
if there's a crime

313
00:13:07.430 --> 00:13:08.910
until we know who
the father is.

314
00:13:08.954 --> 00:13:10.520
- We think it was an adult?

315
00:13:10.564 --> 00:13:12.000
- She won't say. and unless
we can get her

316
00:13:12.044 --> 00:13:13.393
to take a paternity test.

317
00:13:13.436 --> 00:13:14.742
then we won't know who
the father is

318
00:13:14.785 --> 00:13:16.701
and we don't know
if she was raped.

319
00:13:16.745 --> 00:13:18.921
- You realize her attorney's
going to argue some form of

320
00:13:18.965 --> 00:13:20.053
my body my choice?

321
00:13:20.096 --> 00:13:21.576
- She's 13 years old. Peter.

322
00:13:21.619 --> 00:13:23.230
- And then we're gonna get hit
with a heavy dose

323
00:13:23.273 --> 00:13:25.276
of her right to privacy.

324
00:13:25.320 --> 00:13:27.583
- Is there a chance?

325
00:13:27.626 --> 00:13:30.716
Just--is there even a chance?

326
00:13:30.760 --> 00:13:33.937
- As long as judges are human.
there's a chance.

327
00:13:35.984 --> 00:13:40.031
- Hey. Stone got the motion
put on tomorrow's calendar.

328
00:13:40.075 --> 00:13:42.904
- Good for you.

329
00:13:42.947 --> 00:13:44.601
- Well. don't be so excited
about it.

330
00:13:44.644 --> 00:13:47.953
- What I meant was. Liv.
is it's good for you.

331
00:13:47.997 --> 00:13:50.695
I'm not so sure how good
it is for Mackenzie.

332
00:13:50.738 --> 00:13:52.784
- There's a chance that we're
looking at statutory rape.

333
00:13:52.827 --> 00:13:54.568
- There's a chance we're not.

334
00:13:54.612 --> 00:13:57.485
I mean. Dreyfus
offered up his DNA.

335
00:13:57.529 --> 00:13:59.052
Well. what can I say?

336
00:13:59.096 --> 00:14:00.619
It makes my skin crawl
a little bit thinking about

337
00:14:00.662 --> 00:14:02.360
a court violating
a minor's privacy.

338
00:14:02.403 --> 00:14:04.710
You know. because let's say
for the sake of argument that

339
00:14:04.753 --> 00:14:08.976
the father is Zack or Jake or
some other middle schooler.

340
00:14:09.020 --> 00:14:10.456
Why ruin his life too?

341
00:14:10.499 --> 00:14:12.197
- I didn't know a baby
ruined anyone's life.

342
00:14:12.240 --> 00:14:13.459
- You know what I mean.

343
00:14:13.502 --> 00:14:15.462
You know. maybe she--she's--

344
00:14:15.505 --> 00:14:17.377
she's keeping the burden off
another 13-year-old.

345
00:14:17.420 --> 00:14:20.684
Maybe she's being righteous
by--by keeping him in the dark.

346
00:14:20.728 --> 00:14:22.643
- And if it's a 40-year-old
drama teacher?

347
00:14:22.686 --> 00:14:24.775
- [sighs]
I mean. did you?

348
00:14:24.819 --> 00:14:26.300
- Did I what?

349
00:14:26.343 --> 00:14:27.692
- Yeah. when you were pregnant.

350
00:14:27.736 --> 00:14:29.259
did you let the father
know before you...

351
00:14:29.303 --> 00:14:30.565
- Before I what?

352
00:14:30.608 --> 00:14:32.132
- [sighs]
You're making me say it?

353
00:14:32.175 --> 00:14:33.394
We were standing right here

354
00:14:33.437 --> 00:14:35.701
and you told me you
had an abortion.

355
00:14:37.181 --> 00:14:39.401
- I-I never said that.

356
00:14:39.444 --> 00:14:41.664
- So I dreamt it?

357
00:14:41.707 --> 00:14:44.841
- No. Amanda.
what I said was...

358
00:14:44.884 --> 00:14:50.108
is that regret can be
an awful thing to live with

359
00:14:50.152 --> 00:14:53.416
and so you assumed...

360
00:14:54.765 --> 00:14:57.595
- Yeah. and you let me.

361
00:14:57.638 --> 00:15:00.511
- I did.
and I'm sorry. Amanda.

362
00:15:00.554 --> 00:15:03.383
It's just--it's a
very complicated story

363
00:15:03.427 --> 00:15:05.386
and I didn't want
to get into it.

364
00:15:05.430 --> 00:15:06.953
- So it's a privacy thing.

365
00:15:06.997 --> 00:15:09.042
which--which was
my argument to begin with

366
00:15:09.086 --> 00:15:10.696
in this conversation.

367
00:15:10.739 --> 00:15:12.915
All right?
- Okay.

368
00:15:13.916 --> 00:15:16.181
- What the hell?
Mackenzie.

369
00:15:16.224 --> 00:15:17.878
- I'm so sorry. I didn't--

370
00:15:17.921 --> 00:15:19.358
- Are you this Lieutenant
she's yapping about?

371
00:15:19.401 --> 00:15:21.142
- I'm Lieutenant Benson.

372
00:15:21.186 --> 00:15:22.361
- $19.65.
- I'm sorry?

373
00:15:22.404 --> 00:15:23.884
- That's what was on the meter.

374
00:15:23.927 --> 00:15:25.365
Who takes a cab
without money?

375
00:15:25.408 --> 00:15:26.888
- Here.
Thanks.

376
00:15:26.931 --> 00:15:29.978
- A tip would be appreciated.
- [scoffs]

377
00:15:30.022 --> 00:15:31.719
- I hope you learned something.
young lady.

378
00:15:31.762 --> 00:15:33.373
- I'm so sorry.
I was gonna call.

379
00:15:33.416 --> 00:15:35.070
It's just
Garrett took my phone.

380
00:15:35.115 --> 00:15:37.073
- Okay. that's why
we're here. Mackenzie.

381
00:15:37.117 --> 00:15:38.248
Are you okay?
What's--

382
00:15:38.292 --> 00:15:39.554
what's going on?
- I don't know.

383
00:15:39.597 --> 00:15:43.123
I told Garrett
that it was Mr. Dreyfus.

384
00:15:46.388 --> 00:15:48.781
- What did he say?

385
00:15:48.825 --> 00:15:51.567
- He was so upset.
Mr. D's a good guy.

386
00:15:51.610 --> 00:15:53.003
I didn't want him
to get in trouble.

387
00:15:53.047 --> 00:15:54.918
I just thought that.
with the blood test.

388
00:15:54.961 --> 00:15:57.965
you'd figure out anyway
and I'm sorry about the money.

389
00:15:58.009 --> 00:15:59.750
- Mackenzie. where is
your stepfather right now?

390
00:15:59.793 --> 00:16:02.013
- I don't know.
I told him and he left.

391
00:16:02.057 --> 00:16:03.667
- Did he say where
he was going?

392
00:16:03.710 --> 00:16:06.105
- No. he slammed the door.
He was so mad.

393
00:16:06.149 --> 00:16:08.107
- Okay. honey. I want you to
have a seat right here.

394
00:16:08.151 --> 00:16:10.544
I'll be right back.

395
00:16:14.592 --> 00:16:17.552
[police sirens wail]

396
00:16:17.596 --> 00:16:20.555
[tense music]

397
00:16:20.599 --> 00:16:27.694
♪

398
00:16:29.478 --> 00:16:31.219
NYPD!

399
00:16:31.263 --> 00:16:33.482
Mr. Dreyfus?

400
00:16:45.192 --> 00:16:46.410
Mr. Howard.

401
00:16:46.454 --> 00:16:48.891
Mr. Howard.
put the weapon down now.

402
00:17:00.556 --> 00:17:02.688
- No.

403
00:17:02.732 --> 00:17:05.127
- I didn't mean to.

404
00:17:06.171 --> 00:17:07.520
- [sighs]

405
00:17:11.133 --> 00:17:11.307
.

406
00:17:11.350 --> 00:17:14.832
- I was so angry.
I didn't know what I was doing.

407
00:17:14.875 --> 00:17:17.227
Has your blood ever boiled.
Mr. Stone?

408
00:17:17.270 --> 00:17:21.274
She's only 13.
I mean. how could he?

409
00:17:22.145 --> 00:17:24.364
- Please tell us what happened.
Mr. Howard.

410
00:17:25.584 --> 00:17:27.194
- Go on.

411
00:17:27.238 --> 00:17:29.588
- Uh. Mack told me about
the theater teacher.

412
00:17:29.631 --> 00:17:31.720
uh. Mr. Dreyfus.

413
00:17:31.764 --> 00:17:36.030
And I had met him last spring
after the Easter play.

414
00:17:36.073 --> 00:17:38.946
and all I could think about
is his hairy body

415
00:17:38.989 --> 00:17:42.732
on top of my sw--my sweet...

416
00:17:42.776 --> 00:17:44.343
[chuckles]

417
00:17:44.386 --> 00:17:45.867
- Okay.

418
00:17:45.910 --> 00:17:49.958
Um. what did you say
to Mr. Dreyfus?

419
00:17:51.960 --> 00:17:54.702
- I asked him how could he.

420
00:17:54.745 --> 00:17:59.055
I asked him
what kind of animal...

421
00:17:59.098 --> 00:18:01.753
and I told him there was
a special place in hell

422
00:18:01.797 --> 00:18:03.668
waiting just for him.

423
00:18:03.712 --> 00:18:05.802
- What did he say to you?

424
00:18:05.845 --> 00:18:08.544
- [sighs]
He told me to leave

425
00:18:08.587 --> 00:18:12.417
and I said I wouldn't until he
told me to my face what he did.

426
00:18:12.461 --> 00:18:14.811
- And did he?

427
00:18:14.854 --> 00:18:16.466
- He just smiled.

428
00:18:16.509 --> 00:18:18.903
This cruel heartless smile
and he told me to leave again

429
00:18:18.946 --> 00:18:21.514
and I couldn't move.

430
00:18:21.558 --> 00:18:26.433
And I'm so filled with--with
anger. with so much hate.

431
00:18:26.477 --> 00:18:29.828
And he--he pushed me.
I-I pushed him back.

432
00:18:29.871 --> 00:18:32.396
and--and then--
[sniffs]

433
00:18:33.832 --> 00:18:36.183
- And then what. Mr. Howard?

434
00:18:37.489 --> 00:18:40.056
- I saw the trophy.
It was on the coffee table.

435
00:18:40.100 --> 00:18:43.146
I grabbed it and I swung.

436
00:18:46.063 --> 00:18:48.936
And as soon as I saw him
lying there. not moving.

437
00:18:48.979 --> 00:18:51.243
I was filled with guilt.

438
00:18:53.941 --> 00:18:57.075
One sin does
not justify another and--

439
00:18:57.119 --> 00:18:59.556
- I think that's enough.

440
00:19:01.732 --> 00:19:05.694
Obviously he was under
extreme emotional distress.

441
00:19:05.737 --> 00:19:08.392
- I can't go lower than
Man Two.

442
00:19:09.654 --> 00:19:10.699
- How much?

443
00:19:10.742 --> 00:19:12.483
- Two years. one probation.

444
00:19:12.527 --> 00:19:13.963
- You're kidding!

445
00:19:14.006 --> 00:19:15.270
- He killed a man.

446
00:19:15.313 --> 00:19:17.663
- And what jury is
going to convict him?

447
00:19:17.707 --> 00:19:20.275
Thanks but no thanks.

448
00:19:24.714 --> 00:19:26.020
- There's a Mr. Woodward here.

449
00:19:26.064 --> 00:19:27.892
Says it's about
the Quentin Dreyfus murder.

450
00:19:27.935 --> 00:19:30.068
- Send him in.

451
00:19:33.637 --> 00:19:34.855
- Thank you for seeing me.

452
00:19:34.899 --> 00:19:36.771
- What can I do for you.
Mr. Woodward?

453
00:19:36.815 --> 00:19:39.339
- Uh. I knew Quentin Dreyfus.

454
00:19:39.383 --> 00:19:41.515
In fact.
I knew him very well.

455
00:19:41.559 --> 00:19:44.431
- Have a seat.
I'm sorry for your loss.

456
00:19:44.475 --> 00:19:46.042
- Can I get you something?
Water?

457
00:19:46.086 --> 00:19:49.089
- Oh. I'm fine.

458
00:19:49.132 --> 00:19:52.222
Well. like I'll ever
be fine again.

459
00:19:52.266 --> 00:19:55.270
I loved Quentin
and he loved me.

460
00:19:57.925 --> 00:19:59.230
- I see.

461
00:19:59.274 --> 00:20:00.754
- What those people
are saying about him.

462
00:20:00.797 --> 00:20:04.714
that he had sex with
that student. it can't be true.

463
00:20:04.758 --> 00:20:07.152
He wouldn't.

464
00:20:07.196 --> 00:20:09.241
- Were you in
a serious relationship?

465
00:20:09.285 --> 00:20:12.462
- We were going
to get married next summer.

466
00:20:13.811 --> 00:20:17.250
- I'm sorry. you've--you've
caught me completely off guard.

467
00:20:17.294 --> 00:20:19.035
Uh. nobody told me that--

468
00:20:19.078 --> 00:20:21.559
- Of course. of course
they didn't--they didn't know.

469
00:20:21.603 --> 00:20:23.605
Do you know what would happen
to him at that school

470
00:20:23.648 --> 00:20:26.086
if they found out?

471
00:20:26.130 --> 00:20:27.653
- Did you live together?

472
00:20:27.697 --> 00:20:29.263
- I asked him to move in

473
00:20:29.307 --> 00:20:32.049
but he was afraid a student
or a teacher would find out.

474
00:20:32.092 --> 00:20:33.746
- And there's absolutely
no chance he--

475
00:20:33.790 --> 00:20:35.270
- No.

476
00:20:35.314 --> 00:20:38.273
He's never had sex
with a woman.

477
00:20:39.362 --> 00:20:40.972
- His student.
Mackenzie Tolliver--

478
00:20:41.015 --> 00:20:42.626
- Is lying.

479
00:20:44.454 --> 00:20:47.066
I have no idea why.
but she is.

480
00:20:47.109 --> 00:20:49.634
- Is there anyone else
who can confirm this?

481
00:20:50.548 --> 00:20:53.115
- Would my whole family
be good enough?

482
00:20:53.159 --> 00:20:54.813
All of our friends?

483
00:20:54.856 --> 00:20:59.514
♪

484
00:20:59.558 --> 00:21:04.606
Is it--is it true that he was
killed with a bowling trophy?

485
00:21:06.392 --> 00:21:08.350
- It is.

486
00:21:09.873 --> 00:21:12.441
- The West Village Pin Poppers.

487
00:21:12.485 --> 00:21:16.054
It's an LGBTQ league.
That's where we met.

488
00:21:20.972 --> 00:21:24.802
Anyway. I thought that
you should know.

489
00:21:24.846 --> 00:21:26.283
Not that it matters now.

490
00:21:26.326 --> 00:21:29.504
- Thank you.
Thank you for your time.

491
00:21:31.506 --> 00:21:33.508
[sighs]

492
00:21:39.645 --> 00:21:42.126
Liv. it's Peter.

493
00:21:42.169 --> 00:21:44.520
Something stinks.

494
00:21:46.392 --> 00:21:48.438
- Mr. Kayman. the lawyer.

495
00:21:48.481 --> 00:21:51.179
he said that Garrett would be
out on bail before dinner.

496
00:21:51.223 --> 00:21:53.878
He spoke to Family Services
so I could stay home.

497
00:21:53.921 --> 00:21:55.533
- And you're okay with that?

498
00:21:55.576 --> 00:21:58.623
- With my teacher being dead
or that my stepdad's the one--

499
00:22:00.451 --> 00:22:02.931
It was my fault
that he went over there.

500
00:22:02.975 --> 00:22:04.672
It was an accident. right?

501
00:22:04.716 --> 00:22:07.197
- Mackenzie. it's--
it's normal to be afraid.

502
00:22:07.241 --> 00:22:09.373
to be sad. to be scared.

503
00:22:09.417 --> 00:22:12.115
I can--I can help you
find a place to stay tonight.

504
00:22:12.159 --> 00:22:14.074
- No. no. no.
It's fine.

505
00:22:14.117 --> 00:22:15.424
I'm just--
I'm focusing on dinner.

506
00:22:15.468 --> 00:22:17.034
- What are you making?

507
00:22:17.078 --> 00:22:18.471
- Veal chops.

508
00:22:18.514 --> 00:22:20.473
Garrett's favorite.
[chuckles]

509
00:22:20.516 --> 00:22:24.607
- When I was 13. the only thing
I could make was Pop-Tarts.

510
00:22:24.651 --> 00:22:26.480
- Um. my mom taught me.

511
00:22:26.523 --> 00:22:29.178
She used to cook
every night for him.

512
00:22:30.092 --> 00:22:32.181
- You loved her very much. huh?

513
00:22:32.224 --> 00:22:35.751
- I still do.
I miss her.

514
00:22:37.274 --> 00:22:39.494
- Mackenzie. I need to talk
to you about something.

515
00:22:39.537 --> 00:22:41.278
- No. I can't.
Not right now.

516
00:22:41.321 --> 00:22:43.236
- Sweetie. it's important.

517
00:22:43.280 --> 00:22:46.153
I'm not sure that
you're telling me the truth

518
00:22:46.197 --> 00:22:48.416
about Mr. Dreyfus.

519
00:22:49.243 --> 00:22:50.810
- I am.

520
00:22:51.811 --> 00:22:53.073
- Okay.

521
00:22:53.117 --> 00:22:54.640
Well. then. would you mind
telling me

522
00:22:54.684 --> 00:22:57.557
exactly how it happened.

523
00:22:57.601 --> 00:22:58.950
All right?

524
00:22:58.993 --> 00:23:02.083
You said that
you didn't know his name

525
00:23:02.127 --> 00:23:03.955
and you said that you met
in Whole Foods.

526
00:23:03.998 --> 00:23:05.914
- Well. I didn't want
to get him in trouble.

527
00:23:05.958 --> 00:23:07.437
- Well. that's understandable

528
00:23:07.481 --> 00:23:10.571
but I think maybe
there's somebody else

529
00:23:10.615 --> 00:23:12.225
that you don't want to get
in trouble.

530
00:23:12.268 --> 00:23:15.446
- You're clueless.
- Well. then clue me in.

531
00:23:19.189 --> 00:23:21.931
Mackenzie. do you feel safe

532
00:23:21.975 --> 00:23:24.586
when you're at home
with Garrett?

533
00:23:24.630 --> 00:23:27.155
- He's not gonna hurt me.

534
00:23:28.417 --> 00:23:31.638
Wait. you think he put
this baby in me?

535
00:23:31.681 --> 00:23:33.117
- Did he?

536
00:23:33.161 --> 00:23:34.771
- It was Mr. Dreyfus.

537
00:23:34.815 --> 00:23:37.035
Now that he's dead.
I can't even prove it.

538
00:23:37.079 --> 00:23:39.255
- Well. we don't think
that it was him.

539
00:23:39.298 --> 00:23:43.781
And if Garrett killed Dreyfus
because of your lie...

540
00:23:43.825 --> 00:23:46.655
- It only matters if he knows
I was lying. right?

541
00:23:53.836 --> 00:23:55.186
I have to go.

542
00:23:55.229 --> 00:23:56.535
Garrett doesn't like it
when I'm late.

543
00:24:00.147 --> 00:24:02.062
- Well. she's right.

544
00:24:02.106 --> 00:24:04.761
If Garrett didn't know
she was lying about Dreyfus.

545
00:24:04.804 --> 00:24:06.067
he still has a defense.

546
00:24:06.111 --> 00:24:09.723
- My point is--is that
she's in eighth grade.

547
00:24:09.767 --> 00:24:11.725
- You think she wanted Garrett
to kill Dreyfus?

548
00:24:11.769 --> 00:24:14.510
- A teenager? I don't think
she thinks anything through.

549
00:24:14.554 --> 00:24:16.644
But I know that
she's protecting somebody

550
00:24:16.688 --> 00:24:19.734
and my--my gut tells me
that it's Garrett.

551
00:24:19.778 --> 00:24:22.737
- I'll just have to put her
on the stand to find out.

552
00:24:24.521 --> 00:24:25.741
- My Lieutenant and I

553
00:24:25.785 --> 00:24:27.656
rushed over to
Mr. Dreyfus's apartment.

554
00:24:27.700 --> 00:24:29.702
Mr. Dreyfus was on the floor.

555
00:24:29.745 --> 00:24:31.704
He was dead

556
00:24:31.747 --> 00:24:34.010
and Garrett Howard
was sitting on the couch

557
00:24:34.054 --> 00:24:35.883
holding a bowling trophy.

558
00:24:38.537 --> 00:24:42.672
- Was this the trophy.
Detective?

559
00:24:42.716 --> 00:24:44.674
- Yes.

560
00:24:44.718 --> 00:24:48.287
- Huh. I mean this--this could
really do some damage.

561
00:24:48.331 --> 00:24:49.680
- Objection.

562
00:24:49.724 --> 00:24:52.248
- You made your point.
Mr. Stone.

563
00:24:55.339 --> 00:24:57.210
- That's all.

564
00:24:57.254 --> 00:24:59.430
[clears throat]

565
00:25:01.084 --> 00:25:04.653
- When you arrive at
the deceased's apartment.

566
00:25:04.696 --> 00:25:06.568
did Mr. Howard try to run?

567
00:25:06.612 --> 00:25:07.918
- No.

568
00:25:07.961 --> 00:25:11.225
- Did he deny hitting
Mr. Dreyfus with the trophy?

569
00:25:11.269 --> 00:25:14.098
- No.
- Did he say anything to you?

570
00:25:14.141 --> 00:25:16.318
- He said. "I didn't mean to."

571
00:25:18.625 --> 00:25:21.367
- Thank you. Detective.

572
00:25:22.585 --> 00:25:24.413
- Witness may step down.

573
00:25:26.808 --> 00:25:28.723
- The people call
Mackenzie Tolliver.

574
00:25:28.767 --> 00:25:29.724
- Objection.

575
00:25:29.768 --> 00:25:30.899
- She's 13 years old.
Your Honor.

576
00:25:30.943 --> 00:25:32.596
She's perfectly competent
to testify.

577
00:25:32.640 --> 00:25:34.207
- Approach. Your Honor.

578
00:25:34.250 --> 00:25:36.645
- This better be good.
Mr. Kayman.

579
00:25:41.171 --> 00:25:44.000
- [sighs]
- Well?

580
00:25:44.044 --> 00:25:47.265
- Well. this is a bit awkward.

581
00:25:47.309 --> 00:25:49.615
- Objecting without grounds
usually is.

582
00:25:50.660 --> 00:25:52.923
- The proposed witness
is unable to testify

583
00:25:52.967 --> 00:25:56.101
because her communications with
the defendant are privileged.

584
00:25:56.145 --> 00:25:57.755
- I'm sorry. I'm--I'm not aware

585
00:25:57.799 --> 00:25:59.496
of any stepfather/stepdaughter
privilege.

586
00:25:59.539 --> 00:26:01.324
- Neither am I. counselor.

587
00:26:01.367 --> 00:26:05.329
- Yeah. but I'm sure you both
are aware of spousal privilege.

588
00:26:06.765 --> 00:26:08.941
The defendant and Ms. Tolliver.

589
00:26:08.985 --> 00:26:13.903
or should I say Mrs. Howard.
are legally married.

590
00:26:13.946 --> 00:26:16.907
[tense music]

591
00:26:16.950 --> 00:26:19.953
♪

592
00:26:19.997 --> 00:26:22.390
Here is the original
marriage license.

593
00:26:22.434 --> 00:26:25.089
It's from Missouri.

594
00:26:25.132 --> 00:26:28.354
And a copy for you.

595
00:26:34.839 --> 00:26:37.190
- Well...

596
00:26:37.233 --> 00:26:39.018
that's enough for today.

597
00:26:43.370 --> 00:26:44.588
We're adjourned.

598
00:26:44.632 --> 00:26:46.722
[gavel thuds]

599
00:26:48.202 --> 00:26:49.725
- [sighs]

600
00:26:53.424 --> 00:26:53.642
.

601
00:26:53.685 --> 00:26:56.298
- The marriage license was duly
recorded in a courthouse

602
00:26:56.341 --> 00:26:59.388
in Caruthersville. Missouri.
on August 27. 2018.

603
00:26:59.431 --> 00:27:02.695
- It's a year after
her mother died.

604
00:27:02.739 --> 00:27:04.915
She was too young to even know
what marriage means.

605
00:27:04.959 --> 00:27:06.483
- It's bonkers.

606
00:27:06.526 --> 00:27:08.441
Almost 20 states have
no minimum age for marriage.

607
00:27:08.485 --> 00:27:11.618
Over 200.000 kids
were married since 1999.

608
00:27:11.662 --> 00:27:13.229
some as young as 11.

609
00:27:13.272 --> 00:27:15.667
Turns out Caruthersville is a
real hot spot for child brides.

610
00:27:15.710 --> 00:27:17.016
- So this marriage is legal.

611
00:27:17.060 --> 00:27:19.149
- Maybe.
Under the Missouri statute.

612
00:27:19.192 --> 00:27:21.281
a child under 16
can get married

613
00:27:21.325 --> 00:27:23.501
as long as they have the
consent of a blood relative.

614
00:27:23.544 --> 00:27:24.894
- Okay.

615
00:27:24.937 --> 00:27:26.505
Now this consent was
executed by Marcus Tolliver.

616
00:27:26.548 --> 00:27:27.854
That's Mackenzie's father.

617
00:27:27.898 --> 00:27:29.856
- He's a junkie
who's in the wind.

618
00:27:29.900 --> 00:27:31.118
- Right. he was in Rikers.

619
00:27:31.162 --> 00:27:32.380
he did three years
for attempted burglary.

620
00:27:32.424 --> 00:27:33.817
he got released
four years ago.

621
00:27:33.860 --> 00:27:35.297
and then nothing until this.

622
00:27:35.341 --> 00:27:38.518
- Track him down.
Relatives. family. friends.

623
00:27:38.561 --> 00:27:41.390
- She got a. uh. she's got
an aunt in Connecticut.

624
00:27:41.434 --> 00:27:43.262
Penelope Archer.

625
00:27:43.305 --> 00:27:45.265
- Go.

626
00:27:47.136 --> 00:27:48.355
- Why didn't she call me?

627
00:27:48.398 --> 00:27:49.878
She didn't do anything wrong.

628
00:27:49.922 --> 00:27:51.967
Garrett killed that man.

629
00:27:52.011 --> 00:27:54.013
She's moving in with me
and that is it.

630
00:27:54.056 --> 00:27:55.885
- It's--it's not that simple.

631
00:27:55.929 --> 00:27:57.452
- What are you talking about?

632
00:27:57.495 --> 00:27:59.541
I will go to the courthouse
and I will tell them that--

633
00:27:59.584 --> 00:28:01.891
- Um. listen.

634
00:28:01.935 --> 00:28:04.633
she and Garrett are married.

635
00:28:04.676 --> 00:28:06.070
- She's 13.

636
00:28:06.114 --> 00:28:09.073
- Apparently that's legal
in Missouri.

637
00:28:09.117 --> 00:28:11.467
- Missouri.
- Yeah. that's not all.

638
00:28:11.510 --> 00:28:13.425
She's pregnant.

639
00:28:13.469 --> 00:28:15.385
- With his child?

640
00:28:15.428 --> 00:28:18.083
- That's what they're saying.

641
00:28:19.476 --> 00:28:21.347
- Oh. my God.

642
00:28:22.566 --> 00:28:25.047
Oh. that sick pervert.

643
00:28:25.090 --> 00:28:27.050
- Were you and Mackenzie close?

644
00:28:29.487 --> 00:28:31.228
- I'm her aunt.

645
00:28:35.624 --> 00:28:38.149
When Angela died.
I tried to get closer.

646
00:28:38.192 --> 00:28:42.153
I. you know. we'd go down into
the city for girls' trips.

647
00:28:42.196 --> 00:28:44.416
shopping. brunch.

648
00:28:45.461 --> 00:28:49.204
But after a while.
she started to shut me out

649
00:28:49.248 --> 00:28:51.076
and now I know why.

650
00:28:51.119 --> 00:28:53.339
I should've known.
- You can't blame yourself.

651
00:28:53.382 --> 00:28:55.429
- No. she should've
been living here.

652
00:28:55.472 --> 00:28:57.300
It's not like Garrett
was even family.

653
00:28:57.344 --> 00:28:58.911
- Well. speaking of which.

654
00:28:58.954 --> 00:29:01.130
we're--we're trying to locate
Mackenzie's father.

655
00:29:01.174 --> 00:29:03.002
- [chuckles]

656
00:29:03.045 --> 00:29:05.091
Now there's a first class
screw-up for you.

657
00:29:05.134 --> 00:29:07.703
Seems like Angela had
a thing for them.

658
00:29:07.746 --> 00:29:09.400
He went to prison. you know.

659
00:29:09.444 --> 00:29:11.620
- Have you spoken to him
since he was released?

660
00:29:11.663 --> 00:29:16.234
- He came here asking for money
after we buried Angela.

661
00:29:16.278 --> 00:29:18.802
"Pay up
or I'll take Mackenzie."

662
00:29:18.845 --> 00:29:20.630
- So you paid him.

663
00:29:20.673 --> 00:29:22.458
- Christ.

664
00:29:22.501 --> 00:29:24.068
You know. to think
that I thought

665
00:29:24.112 --> 00:29:27.203
Mackenzie would be better off
with Garrett.

666
00:29:27.246 --> 00:29:29.031
I gave him about
five grand in cash

667
00:29:29.074 --> 00:29:31.598
and I told him never
come back here.

668
00:29:33.209 --> 00:29:36.996
And when he's broke.
he just calls.

669
00:29:37.040 --> 00:29:39.564
- So you have his address.

670
00:29:39.607 --> 00:29:41.348
- I have an old one.

671
00:29:41.392 --> 00:29:43.394
Uh. he's not exactly the type

672
00:29:43.437 --> 00:29:46.006
that stays in one place
for long.

673
00:29:46.050 --> 00:29:47.747
[handle rattling]

674
00:29:51.577 --> 00:29:52.795
- Who are you?

675
00:29:52.839 --> 00:29:54.449
- NYPD--I need to talk
to Marcus Tolliver.

676
00:29:54.493 --> 00:29:57.758
- Never heard of him.
- Lola. I need a lighter.

677
00:29:57.801 --> 00:29:59.542
- Shall I introduce you?

678
00:29:59.586 --> 00:30:00.630
- She's a cop.

679
00:30:00.674 --> 00:30:03.416
What the hell
did you do this time?

680
00:30:03.459 --> 00:30:06.072
- I'm here to talk to you
about your daughter.

681
00:30:06.115 --> 00:30:08.944
- You have a kid?
- Oh. shut up.

682
00:30:08.988 --> 00:30:10.337
Did something happen
to Mack?

683
00:30:10.380 --> 00:30:13.209
- Well. first of all.
she's pregnant.

684
00:30:13.253 --> 00:30:14.776
- Just like her mom.

685
00:30:14.819 --> 00:30:16.692
- Oh. that's okay though
'cause she's married. right?

686
00:30:16.735 --> 00:30:18.128
- Look. she said
she loved the guy.

687
00:30:18.172 --> 00:30:19.477
What do you want from me?

688
00:30:19.521 --> 00:30:21.131
- Yeah. I would ask
what you were thinking.

689
00:30:21.175 --> 00:30:22.567
but I don't--I don't see much
of that going on here.

690
00:30:22.611 --> 00:30:24.221
- Oh. you come to
my house to insult me?

691
00:30:24.265 --> 00:30:26.224
- How much did Garrett pay you?
- For what?

692
00:30:26.268 --> 00:30:28.096
- Are you stuck on stupid.
Marcus?

693
00:30:28.139 --> 00:30:31.708
How much did he pay you
to sign the consent form?

694
00:30:31.751 --> 00:30:33.188
Fine.

695
00:30:33.231 --> 00:30:34.580
[handcuffs clicking]

696
00:30:34.624 --> 00:30:36.540
- Okay. okay.

697
00:30:37.845 --> 00:30:39.978
He gave me ten grand.

698
00:30:40.022 --> 00:30:47.247
♪

699
00:30:49.119 --> 00:30:50.555
- They're married?

700
00:30:50.598 --> 00:30:52.948
- Under Missouri law.
it's perfectly legal.

701
00:30:52.992 --> 00:30:55.735
The duly authorized license
is attached to our papers.

702
00:30:55.778 --> 00:30:58.390
- I saw it.
That doesn't mean I believe it.

703
00:30:58.433 --> 00:31:00.522
And I hope that one of you
will tell me why

704
00:31:00.566 --> 00:31:02.133
I don't have to give
full faith and credit

705
00:31:02.176 --> 00:31:04.396
to our sister state's law.

706
00:31:04.439 --> 00:31:06.529
- As noted in our
Motion to Annul.

707
00:31:06.573 --> 00:31:09.097
Missouri Law requires consent
of a blood relative.

708
00:31:09.141 --> 00:31:11.578
It is our position that
Mr. Tolliver was not acting

709
00:31:11.621 --> 00:31:14.102
under his own free will
when he consented.

710
00:31:14.146 --> 00:31:16.671
- How so?
- He was bribed. Your Honor.

711
00:31:16.714 --> 00:31:19.152
- He was hard up.
I gave him some cash.

712
00:31:19.195 --> 00:31:22.285
- How much?
- I don't recall.

713
00:31:23.939 --> 00:31:25.811
- $10.000 is hard to forget.

714
00:31:25.855 --> 00:31:29.119
- And you've changed your mind.
Mr. Tolliver?

715
00:31:29.163 --> 00:31:31.121
- She's only 13. Judge.

716
00:31:31.165 --> 00:31:32.949
I don't know
what I was thinking.

717
00:31:32.992 --> 00:31:34.429
- Okay. Mr. Stone.

718
00:31:34.472 --> 00:31:37.215
I assume that your motion
isn't purely altruistic.

719
00:31:37.259 --> 00:31:38.999
What is your real agenda here?

720
00:31:39.043 --> 00:31:42.046
- Mr. Howard is currently on
trial for Manslaughter.

721
00:31:42.090 --> 00:31:44.962
- And you'd like to call
the young lady as witness.

722
00:31:45.005 --> 00:31:47.835
- The trial is continued until
this matter can be resolved.

723
00:31:47.879 --> 00:31:49.359
- I see.

724
00:31:49.402 --> 00:31:51.143
We'll take a five minute break

725
00:31:51.187 --> 00:31:53.798
and then I will hear
from the bride.

726
00:31:55.322 --> 00:31:57.498
- I think I've always
loved him.

727
00:31:57.542 --> 00:31:59.805
From the first time I saw him.

728
00:31:59.848 --> 00:32:01.502
- When was that?

729
00:32:01.546 --> 00:32:03.809
- When he started dating Mom.

730
00:32:03.852 --> 00:32:05.638
He made us so happy.

731
00:32:05.681 --> 00:32:08.249
He would read me
his books before bed.

732
00:32:08.293 --> 00:32:10.295
His voice was like gold
or something.

733
00:32:10.338 --> 00:32:11.992
I always got goosebumps.

734
00:32:12.035 --> 00:32:16.084
- So you loved him like you
would a rock star?

735
00:32:16.128 --> 00:32:18.347
- No.
- A father?

736
00:32:19.392 --> 00:32:21.307
- I wouldn't know about that.

737
00:32:21.350 --> 00:32:23.831
I've never had a father.

738
00:32:23.874 --> 00:32:26.182
Your Honor. that man
sitting right there.

739
00:32:26.226 --> 00:32:27.531
I don't even know him.

740
00:32:27.575 --> 00:32:29.446
He left before I was even born

741
00:32:29.490 --> 00:32:32.145
and any law that says I need
his permission to be happy

742
00:32:32.188 --> 00:32:34.582
is a stupid law.

743
00:32:34.625 --> 00:32:37.368
And I love him like
a wife loves a husband.

744
00:32:38.674 --> 00:32:42.199
- Like your mother loved him.
- That's right.

745
00:32:44.897 --> 00:32:47.292
- What do you think she would
say about your marriage?

746
00:32:47.336 --> 00:32:49.164
- She'd be happy
that I found a good man.

747
00:32:49.207 --> 00:32:50.339
just like she did.

748
00:32:50.382 --> 00:32:52.210
- You mean the same man.
don't you?

749
00:32:52.254 --> 00:32:54.038
- You don't know anything.

750
00:32:54.081 --> 00:32:57.216
Before Mom died. she told me
to take care of him.

751
00:32:57.260 --> 00:32:58.913
- I doubt this is
what she meant.

752
00:32:58.957 --> 00:33:01.177
- That's enough.
Okay.

753
00:33:02.134 --> 00:33:04.354
A court in the state of
Missouri has already found

754
00:33:04.397 --> 00:33:06.966
that Mr. Tolliver's consent
is valid.

755
00:33:07.009 --> 00:33:10.099
As such. barring fraud.
I am collaterally estopped--

756
00:33:10.143 --> 00:33:13.102
- The father was bribed
to consent. Your Honor.

757
00:33:13.146 --> 00:33:15.758
- Your bribe is Mr. Howard's
charitable contribution.

758
00:33:15.802 --> 00:33:19.414
As I was saying.
I'm collaterally estopped

759
00:33:19.458 --> 00:33:22.112
from finding Mr. Tolliver's
consent invalid.

760
00:33:22.156 --> 00:33:25.072
As such. giving full faith
and credit to Missouri law.

761
00:33:25.115 --> 00:33:28.424
I hold that the marriage
is valid in New York.

762
00:33:28.468 --> 00:33:31.427
[dramatic music]

763
00:33:31.471 --> 00:33:37.434
♪

764
00:33:41.917 --> 00:33:42.134
.

765
00:33:42.178 --> 00:33:44.702
- You're telling me
this marriage is kosher?

766
00:33:44.746 --> 00:33:46.488
- According to Judge Calahan
in the Family Court. it is.

767
00:33:46.531 --> 00:33:49.839
- Ergo Mackenzie cannot testify
against my client.

768
00:33:49.882 --> 00:33:51.928
Because of the sensitive
nature of the relationship

769
00:33:51.971 --> 00:33:53.669
between Mackenzie
and my client.

770
00:33:53.712 --> 00:33:56.847
I move that any mention of said
relationship be prohibited.

771
00:33:56.890 --> 00:33:58.457
- On what grounds?

772
00:33:58.501 --> 00:33:59.893
- Clearly. said relationship

773
00:33:59.937 --> 00:34:01.634
is more prejudicial
than probative.

774
00:34:01.678 --> 00:34:03.984
- Your client is on trial for
killing his wife's teacher.

775
00:34:04.028 --> 00:34:05.987
His marital status
is surely relevant.

776
00:34:06.031 --> 00:34:07.641
- All due respect. Your Honor.

777
00:34:07.685 --> 00:34:09.904
you literally turned green
when I brought it up.

778
00:34:09.948 --> 00:34:13.168
- Truth be told. I'm feeling
a little ill right now.

779
00:34:13.212 --> 00:34:14.692
- That's my point exactly.

780
00:34:14.735 --> 00:34:16.129
A jury will convict him
based on

781
00:34:16.172 --> 00:34:17.957
his alternative
marriage status

782
00:34:18.000 --> 00:34:19.350
and not because of his actions.

783
00:34:19.393 --> 00:34:22.048
- Let's just get this over
with. shall we?

784
00:34:22.091 --> 00:34:24.093
Mr. Kayman's Motion
to exclude references

785
00:34:24.137 --> 00:34:26.749
to the marriage is granted.

786
00:34:26.793 --> 00:34:28.185
We'll pick this up
where we left off.

787
00:34:28.229 --> 00:34:31.058
tomorrow morning.
10:00 a.m.

788
00:34:31.101 --> 00:34:32.886
- Yeah.

789
00:34:32.929 --> 00:34:34.540
Your Honor.

790
00:34:34.583 --> 00:34:36.238
- This is preposterous.

791
00:34:36.282 --> 00:34:39.850
So the law doesn't care
how sick this is.

792
00:34:39.894 --> 00:34:42.070
- Look. bottom line.
to a jury.

793
00:34:42.113 --> 00:34:44.072
Garret's just an irate father
who confronted the man

794
00:34:44.115 --> 00:34:45.901
he thought was sleeping
with his stepdaughter.

795
00:34:45.944 --> 00:34:48.077
- Even though he's the one
that was raping her.

796
00:34:48.120 --> 00:34:51.341
- Yeah. it's not statutory rape
if they're married.

797
00:34:51.385 --> 00:34:53.300
- Bet you thought
you'd never say that.

798
00:34:53.343 --> 00:34:56.173
- Hey. Stone. I looked into
those dates you asked me to.

799
00:34:56.216 --> 00:34:58.306
Mackenzie's first
OB-GYN appointment

800
00:34:58.349 --> 00:35:00.090
was six months
after they were married.

801
00:35:00.133 --> 00:35:02.048
- Which means we can't prove
he married her

802
00:35:02.092 --> 00:35:03.398
just to avoid a rape charge.

803
00:35:03.441 --> 00:35:05.923
- What if he didn't?

804
00:35:08.099 --> 00:35:10.406
- What if he really does
love her?

805
00:35:10.449 --> 00:35:12.973
- Then he'd protect her.

806
00:35:15.629 --> 00:35:17.675
It's worth a shot.

807
00:35:18.502 --> 00:35:21.809
- I want to see them tomorrow
before the trial.

808
00:35:23.898 --> 00:35:26.380
- Okay. we're here.

809
00:35:26.424 --> 00:35:27.773
Why?
You got me.

810
00:35:27.816 --> 00:35:29.470
It's too late for a deal.
Stone.

811
00:35:29.514 --> 00:35:31.951
- I'm considering dropping the
charges against your client.

812
00:35:31.994 --> 00:35:34.214
- Thank you.
- Yeah. no thanks necessary.

813
00:35:34.257 --> 00:35:35.782
He wasn't going to win anyway.

814
00:35:35.825 --> 00:35:37.653
- I'm charging you. Mackenzie.

815
00:35:37.697 --> 00:35:39.176
- What?

816
00:35:39.220 --> 00:35:41.440
- You can't do that.
- Actually. he can.

817
00:35:41.483 --> 00:35:43.572
Mackenzie. you're the one who
put the false idea

818
00:35:43.616 --> 00:35:45.749
in Garrett's head that you
were sleeping with Mr. Dreyfus.

819
00:35:45.793 --> 00:35:47.969
- And it's completely
foreseeable that a stepfather

820
00:35:48.012 --> 00:35:49.318
would take vengeance
against the man

821
00:35:49.362 --> 00:35:51.407
sexually preying
on his stepdaughter.

822
00:35:51.451 --> 00:35:54.149
[tense music]

823
00:35:54.192 --> 00:35:57.458
- Especially when the two
of you are so close.

824
00:35:57.501 --> 00:36:01.636
♪

825
00:36:01.679 --> 00:36:03.159
- Do something!

826
00:36:03.202 --> 00:36:04.595
- Stop!

827
00:36:04.639 --> 00:36:05.945
- Mackenzie. you should know

828
00:36:05.989 --> 00:36:08.470
that your baby will be born
in prison.

829
00:36:11.864 --> 00:36:14.606
- Stop!
- Don't say anything!

830
00:36:14.650 --> 00:36:16.522
- I killed Dreyfus. I had to.

831
00:36:16.566 --> 00:36:17.741
- No. you didn't!

832
00:36:17.784 --> 00:36:19.264
He wasn't going
to say anything!

833
00:36:19.307 --> 00:36:21.135
- You should never have
told him about us.

834
00:36:21.179 --> 00:36:22.833
- He was my friend.

835
00:36:22.876 --> 00:36:25.139
After the cops talked to him.
they told him I was pregnant.

836
00:36:25.183 --> 00:36:27.491
He came to me.
he was worried about me.

837
00:36:27.534 --> 00:36:30.102
but he promised
not to say anything.

838
00:36:30.145 --> 00:36:31.886
- I lost your mother.

839
00:36:31.930 --> 00:36:35.761
I couldn't take the chance that
anyone would find out about us.

840
00:36:35.804 --> 00:36:37.240
- But your marriage was legal.

841
00:36:37.284 --> 00:36:39.025
There's nothing
to be ashamed of. unless...

842
00:36:39.068 --> 00:36:41.157
- I am not ashamed!

843
00:36:43.377 --> 00:36:44.813
You look at her.

844
00:36:44.857 --> 00:36:47.643
How could you not fall in love
with someone so beautiful

845
00:36:47.687 --> 00:36:50.124
and so sweet?

846
00:36:50.167 --> 00:36:53.170
An angel sent from heaven
to bless my life.

847
00:36:53.214 --> 00:36:55.870
to bless me.
and look at us now.

848
00:36:55.913 --> 00:36:59.439
Your stupid laws
have ruined us.

849
00:37:01.092 --> 00:37:05.358
My whole life
I've searched for real love

850
00:37:05.402 --> 00:37:06.534
and I found it.

851
00:37:06.577 --> 00:37:08.187
What was I supposed to do?

852
00:37:08.231 --> 00:37:12.453
- Waiting till she was 18
would've been a good start.

853
00:37:12.496 --> 00:37:13.845
- About that deal?

854
00:37:13.889 --> 00:37:16.370
- Man One. he does 20.

855
00:37:16.414 --> 00:37:17.937
- Max is 25.

856
00:37:17.981 --> 00:37:18.938
- Take it or I'll add
statutory rape.

857
00:37:18.982 --> 00:37:20.679
- You--you can't prove that.

858
00:37:20.723 --> 00:37:23.073
- There's no spousal privilege
when child abuse is involved.

859
00:37:23.116 --> 00:37:26.425
- What jury is going
to believe that you waited

860
00:37:26.469 --> 00:37:28.645
until you were married
to sleep with someone

861
00:37:28.688 --> 00:37:33.258
that you loved so much?

862
00:37:33.301 --> 00:37:34.999
Get this douche out of here.

863
00:37:35.042 --> 00:37:36.567
- No. no. please!
Don't do this!

864
00:37:36.610 --> 00:37:38.612
- Baby. I love you. I love you.
- No. no!

865
00:37:38.656 --> 00:37:40.875
- Listen to me.
you have to let him go.

866
00:37:40.919 --> 00:37:43.138
Let him--

867
00:37:44.096 --> 00:37:47.274
- [sobbing]

868
00:37:48.841 --> 00:37:56.110
♪

869
00:38:06.034 --> 00:38:07.992
What are you doing here?
- I care about you.

870
00:38:08.036 --> 00:38:09.690
- Right. that's why
you ruined my life?

871
00:38:09.733 --> 00:38:11.909
- [scoffs] He killed
your friend. Mackenzie.

872
00:38:11.953 --> 00:38:14.172
He manipulated you.
- I wanted to.

873
00:38:14.216 --> 00:38:16.872
- No. he made you think
that you wanted to.

874
00:38:16.915 --> 00:38:18.961
- You're just jealous.

875
00:38:19.004 --> 00:38:21.311
- Mackenzie.
I didn't know your mother.

876
00:38:21.354 --> 00:38:24.793
but I guarantee you she
wouldn't have approved of you

877
00:38:24.836 --> 00:38:27.840
getting married at this age.
- How do you know?

878
00:38:27.884 --> 00:38:29.320
- Because I know that
she loved you

879
00:38:29.363 --> 00:38:33.106
and I know she would've done
anything to protect you.

880
00:38:33.150 --> 00:38:36.850
Just like I would do anything
to protect my son

881
00:38:36.894 --> 00:38:39.157
and keep him happy
and keep him safe.

882
00:38:39.200 --> 00:38:42.769
Just like you would do anything
to protect your baby.

883
00:38:43.596 --> 00:38:46.557
Honey. I know that this is
hard to see right now.

884
00:38:46.600 --> 00:38:48.167
- Why?
Because I'm just a kid?

885
00:38:48.210 --> 00:38:49.995
- No. honey.
that's a good thing.

886
00:38:50.038 --> 00:38:51.562
That's a great thing

887
00:38:51.605 --> 00:38:54.521
and it's--it's a mistake
to run away from that.

888
00:38:54.565 --> 00:38:57.003
- I'm not stupid. you know.
- I know that.

889
00:38:57.046 --> 00:38:59.614
But you were vulnerable

890
00:38:59.658 --> 00:39:02.530
and Garrett took
advantage of that.

891
00:39:04.097 --> 00:39:06.187
- I took good care of him.
- Honey. I know.

892
00:39:06.230 --> 00:39:10.583
- When he looked at me.
it made me feel...

893
00:39:10.626 --> 00:39:13.368
- Wanted?
Needed?

894
00:39:13.411 --> 00:39:16.633
- Loved?
Like I was a real woman.

895
00:39:17.895 --> 00:39:19.810
- Oh. sweetheart.

896
00:39:19.854 --> 00:39:22.596
But. sweetheart. you're not...

897
00:39:22.639 --> 00:39:25.600
yet.

898
00:39:25.643 --> 00:39:28.385
The truth of the matter is
you should've been out

899
00:39:28.428 --> 00:39:31.693
riding bikes with your friends.

900
00:39:31.736 --> 00:39:34.870
gossiping with your friends.

901
00:39:34.913 --> 00:39:39.876
and Garrett took something
from you that is...

902
00:39:39.919 --> 00:39:43.531
that is irreplaceable.

903
00:39:43.575 --> 00:39:45.665
- My childhood?

904
00:39:45.709 --> 00:39:48.625
[somber music]

905
00:39:48.668 --> 00:39:51.279
- Mackenzie. but what
I can promise you...

906
00:39:51.323 --> 00:39:53.717
♪

907
00:39:53.760 --> 00:39:57.243
Is the way your baby
is gonna look at you.

908
00:39:57.286 --> 00:40:01.247
It's going to make you feel...

909
00:40:01.290 --> 00:40:03.684
more loved.

910
00:40:03.728 --> 00:40:08.124
more needed than
you can ever imagine.

911
00:40:10.431 --> 00:40:13.652
But it's an awesome
responsibility.

912
00:40:16.656 --> 00:40:18.527
- I bet you're a good mom.
- [chuckles]

913
00:40:18.570 --> 00:40:23.358
I don't know.
It's just trial and error.

914
00:40:24.315 --> 00:40:27.363
- At least you didn't die.

915
00:40:31.672 --> 00:40:33.499
- Sweetheart.

916
00:40:33.543 --> 00:40:35.938
Oh. sweetheart.
Sweetheart.

917
00:40:35.981 --> 00:40:40.769
- [sobbing]
- Oh. honey.

918
00:40:40.812 --> 00:40:47.646
♪

919
00:40:52.477 --> 00:40:52.695
.

920
00:40:52.738 --> 00:40:55.307
[dramatic music]

921
00:40:55.350 --> 00:41:02.618
♪

922
00:41:21.552 --> 00:41:24.730
[wolf howling]
